    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-04T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-04T14:00:00-05:00" n="477"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2395: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-04T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 4, 1919, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your September 1, 4 p.m.</p>
                <p>In view of understanding between the Department and Japanese Embassy covered by
                    Department’s November 16, 6 p.m., and December 5, 8 p.m.,<note n="16"
                        xml:id="d477fn16">
                        <ref target="frus1918#pg_120">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1918, pp. 120</ref> and <ref
                            target="frus1918#pg_135">135</ref>, respectively.</note> and pending
                    proposals for consortium which is intended to include specifically provincial
                    loans the Department believes that it would be impolitic to approve of proposed
                    Hupeh provincial loan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
